e (http://mingw.org/), I see that mingw is \nintended to be:\n\n\"a complete Open Source programming tool set which is suitable for the \ndevelopment of native MS-Windows applications ...\"\n\n... and includes:\n\n\"    \\* A port of the GNU Compiler Collection (GCC), including C, C++, \nADA and Fortran compilers;\n     \\* GNU Binutils for Windows (assembler, linker, archive manager)\n     \\* A command-line installer (mingw-get) for MinGW and MSYS \ndeployment on MS-Windows\n     \\* A GUI wrapper (mingw-get-inst) for the command line installer\"\n\nI don't see the relationship between Term::ReadLine and mingw.  After \nall, Term::ReadLine has been distributed with Perl 5 for a \ndecade-and-a-half:\n\n$ corelist Term::ReadLine\n\nTerm::ReadLine was first released with perl 5.002\n\nIf Perl 5 has been ported to mingw, then Term::ReadLine ought to work \nthere.  If it doesn't, shouldn't this be reported to rt.perl.org?\n\n\u003e I added a preloading of all steps into early Configure.pl so that breakpoints can easily be set.\n\u003e The old handling is not changed.\n\nHave you tried other Configure.pl command-line options, e.g., \n--verbose-step?\n\n\u003e ---\n\u003e \n\u003e Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n\u003e https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/833\n\nThank you very much.\nJim Keenan","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"86141a663c2eb7543d1a51ec6253a1d54de912fd"},"timestamp":1347984363,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDg2NjAwNzE=","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/833#issuecomment-8660071"},"message":"Jim: There is no changed functionality to the Configure.PL user at all.\nI just preload the steps upfront when debugging, instead of waiting for its turn later. \nThis way the debugger knows about the steps and breakpoints earlier and you \ncan even autocomplete your breakpoint.\n\nThe mingw readline problem is related to the inability to get a SIGWINCH signal, resp.\nget the COLUMNS+LINES. This only works on Cygwin or a native cmd.exe console, \nbut not if you ssh into mingw via cygwin.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"86141a663c2eb7543d1a51ec6253a1d54de912fd"},"timestamp":1348445292,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDg4MDQ1MDM=","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/833#issuecomment-8804503"},"message":"Merged in d85def32ec2e3333a271ac550e5f102a6fb1857d\n\nYou can now debug into the first few lines, and do something like c 54, From then on you can tab-expand all breakpoints in steps, like auto::\u003cTAB\u003e","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"86141a663c2eb7543d1a51ec6253a1d54de912fd"},"timestamp":1348445292,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50MjUyMjkyNTA="},"status":2}]}